properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 31 at 3:35PM PST until February 3 at 4:11AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a flood warning
for the following rivers in Washington...

Skykomish River Near Gold Bar affecting Snohomish County
Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County
Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County


Heavy rain overnight with a good punch this morning,and again
tonight, with the addition of a little lower elevation snow melt,
will drive these rivers above flood stage.

The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Snoqualmie River Near Carnation
* from this evening to late Sunday night.
* At  3:15 PM Friday the stage was 51.5 feet.
* Flood stage is 54.0 feet.
* Moderate flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood stage around 8 PM Friday
and crest near 57.8 feet around 4 AM Sunday. The river will fall
below flood stage Sunday afternoon.
* Impact...At 56.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will cause widespread
flooding from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall...
inundating much of the farm land and numerous roads.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
